{"author":{"id":"1949ffc23f11a8cb4f8c42a45c9ad241b49570df9a18687489e9ea78d87c54a3"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772048096,"nonce":"Q5lmoSH/cNaTcX2vEiiCTAYaTwY=","title":"PreToolUse merge hook false positive on protected branch name in paths","message":"The PreToolUse hook that blocks direct git merge into the protected branch uses a regex that matches the protected branch name anywhere in the command text, including in file paths like /worktrees/\u003cprotected-branch\u003e/. This caused git merge --abort to be blocked when run from the protected branch worktree. The hook regex \\b\\${protected}\\b needs to be more targeted to only match branch name arguments, not path components or message body content. Additionally, it fires on the entire bash command string passed to the tool, so even the -m flag content of a git-bug command can trigger it if it contains the word.","files":null}]}